{{about|anatomical references to the salpinx|the musical instrument|salpinx}}

In [[anatomy|anatomical]] contexts, '''salpinx''' is used to refer to a type of tube. Per [[Terminologia Anatomica]], the Latin term "tuba" is usually used to describe most tubes (after the [[Roman tuba]], not the modern [[Tuba]]), but the term "salpinges" and its adjectival derivatives are still sometimes used to describe the following two "tubes":<ref>{{DorlandsDict|seven/000094332|Salpinx}}</ref>

* [[Fallopian tube]] (as in [[mesosalpinx]], [[salpingitis]] and [[hydrosalpinx]])
* [[Eustachian tube]] (as in [[salpingopalatine fold]], [[salpingopharyngeal fold]], and [[salpingopharyngeus muscle]])

